    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "@ImRajdeepB With recent release, Remix provides a way to define the compiler configuration using a json file. Supporting foundry imports on Remix is more about remappings. You can update the compiler settings in `compiler_config` with these remappings to support standard imports in foundry contract:\r\n```\r\n\"remappings\":  [\r\n\t\t\t\"ds-test/=lib/forge-std/lib/ds-test/src/\",\r\n\t\t\t\"forge-std/=lib/forge-std/src/\"\r\n\t\t],\r\n```",
